@startuml
title EVS Electricity Top-Up Flow

actor User
participant "Telegram Bot\n(bot.js)" as Bot
participant "WebApp UI\n/webapp" as WebApp
participant "Express Backend\n(server.js)" as Backend
participant "EVS POS\nevs.com.sg" as EVS
participant "Credit Payment JSP\n120.50.44.233" as CreditJSP
participant "eNETS PaymentListener\nwww.enets.sg" as ENETSListener
participant "eNETS Card Payment\n/GW2/uCredit/pay" as ENETSPay
participant "ORE API\nore.evs.com.sg" as ORE

== Telegram bot flow ==
User -> Bot: /topup
Bot -> User: Ask hostel selection
User -> Bot: Select hostel
Bot -> User: Ask 8-digit Meter ID
User -> Bot: Submit meter ID
Bot -> User: Ask amount ($6–$50)
User -> Bot: Submit amount
Bot -> User: Show WebApp button
User -> WebApp: Open Pay Now

== WebApp loading ==
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp?txtMtrId&txtAmount
Backend -> ORE: getMeterSummary(meterId)
note right: single call returns\naddress + credit_bal
ORE --> Backend: { address, credit_bal }
Backend --> WebApp: Loading page with meter summary

== Purchase bootstrap ==
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/bootstrap?txtMtrId&txtAmount

note over Backend: Promise.all(\n  runPurchaseFlow(...),\n  getMeterSummary(...)\n)

par runPurchaseFlow
  Backend -> EVS: GET /EVSWebPOS/
  EVS --> Backend: Main page

  Backend -> EVS: POST /EVSWebPOS/loginServlet\n(txtMtrId, btnLogin, radRetail)
  EVS --> Backend: Package selection page

  Backend -> EVS: POST /EVSWebPOS/selectOfferServlet\n(txtAmount, hidMinPur, hidMaxPur, ...)
  EVS --> Backend: Payment selection page

  Backend -> EVS: GET /EVSWebPOS/paymentServlet?mode=0&isDedicated=1\n[follows redirects via getFollowRedirects()]
  EVS --> Backend: HTML with merchant_txn_ref

  Backend -> CreditJSP: POST /payment/creditpayment.jsp\n(amt, txn_amount, currency_code,\nmerchant_txn_ref, payment_mode=CC)
  CreditJSP --> Backend: HTML with hidden eNETS message

  Backend -> ENETSListener: POST /enets2/PaymentListener.do\n(message)
  ENETSListener --> Backend: eNETS payment page\n(n, e, netsMid, netsTxnRef)

else getMeterSummary (parallel)
  Backend -> ORE: getMeterSummary(meterId)
  ORE --> Backend: { address, credit_bal }
end

Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, redirectUrl: "/webapp/pay?...params..." }

== Card entry ==
note over WebApp: Client-side redirect\nwindow.location.href = redirectUrl
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/pay?n&e&netsMid&netsTxnRef\n&merchantTxnRef&txtMtrId&txtAmount\n&address&balance&actionUrl
Backend --> WebApp: Custom card payment page\n(loads eNETS RSA scripts from enets.sg)

User -> WebApp: Enter name, email, card no., exp MM/YY, CVV
note over WebApp: RSA encrypt (cardNo + cvv)\nusing n/e from eNETS\nvia jsbn/rsa.js from enets.sg

WebApp -> Backend: POST /webapp/enets_pay\n(enc, netsMid, netsTxnRef, merchantTxnRef,\nmeterId, amount, address, balance, ...)
Backend -> ENETSPay: POST https://www.enets.sg/GW2/uCredit/pay
ENETSPay --> Backend: HTML response

== Result path ==
alt EVS callback form found in eNETS HTML
    note over Backend: extractEvsCallbackFromHtml()\nextracts action, status, id, message
    Backend -> EVS: POST /EVSWebPOS/transSumServlet?status=...&id=...\n(message)
    EVS --> Backend: Final EVS transaction summary HTML
    note over Backend: parseEvsTransactionSummary()\nnormalizeFinalOutcome()
    Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, status, reason,\nmerchantTxnRef, meterId, amount,\naddress, balance }
else fallback receipt parser
    note over Backend: parseEnetsResult()
    Backend --> WebApp: JSON { ok, status, merchantTxnRef,\namount, reason }
end

== Final UI ==
note over WebApp: Client-side redirect\nwindow.location.href = "/webapp/result?" + query
WebApp -> Backend: GET /webapp/result?status&ref&meterId\n&amount&reason&address&balance
Backend --> WebApp: renderFinalResultPage()

alt success
    WebApp --> User: Top-Up Successful ✅
else failure
    WebApp --> User: Top-Up Failed ⚠️
end

@enduml